BARBERTON – The Barberton teenager who went missing from 29 June was found unharmed yesterday. Her father, Bernard Sanderson expressed his thanks to all who assisted in tracking her whereabouts. Tanica Sanderson (14) was found yesterday. “A weight has been lifted off my shoulders knowing that she is safe and unhurt. I would like to thank the police and everyone involved in bringing her home safely.” ALSO READ: Fraudsters hack Department of Education’s system According to a source, the 14-year-old was found in kaNyamazane yesterday and been taken to a place of safety and will subsequently be reunited with her father.